# Tokezly — optional environment overrides. Copy to .env and fill in as needed.
# Per-user cloud API keys are normally entered in-app (Settings + the OS keychain).
# This file is for build/dev overrides only.

# Directory containing libclang.dll, used when building the Whisper engine from source.
# On Windows you can install it (and cmake) user-scope with:  pip install libclang cmake
# LIBCLANG_PATH=C:\path\to\libclang

# Cloud keys (e.g. the free-cloud / Gemini engine) are entered per-user in the
# app's AI Rewrite settings and stored in the OS keychain — they are NOT baked
# into the build. Get a free Gemini key at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey .
# On-device stays the privacy default; the Gemini free tier is used to improve
# Google's models, so the free-cloud engine is an explicit opt-in.
